aka
Dry Summer

Susuz Yaz follows an unrepentantly selfish tobacco farmer who builds a dam
to prevent water from flowing downhill to his neighbors' crops.
Alongside this tale of soul-devouring competition is one of overheated desire,
as a love triangle develops between the farmer, his more decent brother, and
the beautiful villager the latter takes as his bride.
A benchmark of Turkish cinema, this is a visceral, innovatively shot and
vibrantly acted depiction of the horrors of greed.

